1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,980
[2025 Chungnam location incentive
production support project]

2
00:00:10,860 --> 00:00:13,500
[Woo Jihan]

3
00:00:15,760 --> 00:00:18,340
[Shin Jeongyou]

4
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:22,600
[Min Dohee]

5
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:26,680
[Seo Seunghyeon]

6
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:35,020
[Always Meet Again]

7
00:00:36,430 --> 00:00:37,430
Lee Woojin.

8
00:00:37,990 --> 00:00:38,990
Eat this.

9
00:00:48,760 --> 00:00:49,610
Sigh.

10
00:00:50,120 --> 00:00:51,650
Screw that Jang Hyeseong.

11
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:52,560
When he shows up again,

12
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:53,560
he's dead meat!

13
00:00:53,830 --> 00:00:54,610
Hey.

14
00:00:55,290 --> 00:00:56,230
How could you say that

15
00:00:56,230 --> 00:00:57,830
about someone who's missing?

16
00:00:57,830 --> 00:00:58,750
And he's been gone

17
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:00,080
for three whole days.

18
00:01:01,590 --> 00:01:02,920
His family's already reported him

19
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:04,590
missing or as a runaway anyway.

20
00:01:04,590 --> 00:01:05,880
Why are you so worried?

21
00:01:13,470 --> 00:01:14,470
Wait,

22
00:01:15,420 --> 00:01:16,420
are you...

23
00:01:19,990 --> 00:01:20,990
Never mind.

24
00:01:21,970 --> 00:01:22,820
What is it?

25
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:23,610
Nothing.

26
00:01:24,010 --> 00:01:25,940
I'll come again tomorrow morning.

27
00:01:35,789 --> 00:01:36,660
Didn't you say

28
00:01:36,729 --> 00:01:38,789
he suddenly showed up in the art room?

29
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,130
Then this time, I'm sure

30
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:44,500
he'll suddenly show up somewhere again.

31
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:45,840
Don't worry too much.

32
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:39,660
I'm back.

33
00:02:51,690 --> 00:02:52,690
Alright.

34
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:54,680
This is my last chance.

35
00:02:56,090 --> 00:02:57,290
I must change things,

36
00:02:57,690 --> 00:02:58,740
no matter what.

37
00:03:04,530 --> 00:03:07,560
[Episode 5:
Be With You No Matter What]

38
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:16,380
Woojin!

39
00:03:17,510 --> 00:03:18,560
Hey, Lee Woojin!

40
00:03:22,610 --> 00:03:23,610
Jang Hyeseong?

41
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:25,940
Wait right there!

42
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,200
What...

43
00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:07,600
happened to you?

44
00:04:09,340 --> 00:04:10,340
Thank goodness

45
00:04:12,140 --> 00:04:13,380
I get to see you again.

46
00:04:13,870 --> 00:04:15,200
What are you talking about?

47
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,860
You were the one who vanished.

48
00:04:17,730 --> 00:04:19,149
Where did you go?

49
00:04:19,490 --> 00:04:20,730
What happened?

50
00:04:23,170 --> 00:04:24,040
I'm sorry.

51
00:04:24,970 --> 00:04:26,060
What do you mean?

52
00:04:27,990 --> 00:04:28,890
Did

53
00:04:29,010 --> 00:04:30,410
something happen to you?

54
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:34,940
No, nothing.

55
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:37,730
Then why did you suddenly...

56
00:04:37,730 --> 00:04:38,730
I...

57
00:04:42,090 --> 00:04:43,950
I'm sorry for what I said that day.

58
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:51,390
It's OK.

59
00:04:52,030 --> 00:04:53,740
I know you didn't mean it.

60
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:01,470
I'm...

61
00:05:04,490 --> 00:05:05,950
going to stay by your side.

62
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:09,900
To keep you safe from danger,

63
00:05:11,030 --> 00:05:12,370
I will protect you.

64
00:05:15,740 --> 00:05:16,740
Why'd I be in danger—

65
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:17,810
You won't.

66
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:21,950
I'll make sure you're safe.

67
00:05:30,380 --> 00:05:31,420
In any case,

68
00:05:33,980 --> 00:05:34,980
I'd like that.

69
00:05:39,570 --> 00:05:40,580
See you tomorrow.

70
00:05:42,730 --> 00:05:43,730
It's really late.

71
00:05:44,170 --> 00:05:45,170
Go on in.

72
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:47,560
Get home safely.

73
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:48,780
OK.

74
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:07,120
Hey, Jang Hyeseong!

75
00:06:13,850 --> 00:06:14,980
Where have you been?

76
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:23,930
I need to talk to you.

77
00:06:35,690 --> 00:06:38,230
Showing up out of thin air,
and now you want to talk?

78
00:06:38,230 --> 00:06:38,920
Hey.

79
00:06:39,670 --> 00:06:41,270
Did you apologize to Woojin?

80
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:42,440
Because of you, Woojin's been...

81
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:42,930
I know.

82
00:06:44,350 --> 00:06:46,150
He must've been really worried.

83
00:06:47,030 --> 00:06:48,610
I'm sorry to you and Woojin.

84
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,540
Is this what you wanted to say?

85
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:00,440
Please help me.

86
00:07:01,450 --> 00:07:02,520
This might be hard to believe,

87
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:03,040
no,

88
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:04,110
you won't believe me,

89
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:04,850
but you have to.

90
00:07:04,850 --> 00:07:06,710
It's the only way Woojin can live.

91
00:07:06,810 --> 00:07:07,540
What?

92
00:07:08,990 --> 00:07:09,990
Woojin...

93
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:13,270
will die in a week.

94
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:15,510
What the hell is wrong with you?

95
00:07:15,510 --> 00:07:17,440
I told you you wouldn't believe me.

96
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,820
But please believe me.

97
00:07:20,340 --> 00:07:21,520
We must keep Woojin alive.

98
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:22,520
Jang Hyeseong!

99
00:07:23,130 --> 00:07:24,130
Are you serious?

100
00:07:30,180 --> 00:07:31,050
Forget it.

101
00:07:31,330 --> 00:07:33,830
I'm the idiot for
entertaining your nonsense.

102
00:07:33,830 --> 00:07:34,830
Taejun!

103
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:36,700
Wait.

104
00:07:36,980 --> 00:07:37,980
Listen to me.

105
00:07:44,170 --> 00:07:45,170
You will fight with him

106
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:46,370
at school tomorrow.

107
00:07:47,530 --> 00:07:48,580
Two days later,

108
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:50,840
he'll get hurt
while changing a light bulb.

109
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:51,930
And in a week...

110
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,450
He'll really die in a week.

111
00:07:56,450 --> 00:07:58,090
For heaven's sake,
stop with this nonsense,

112
00:07:58,090 --> 00:07:59,000
you crazy bastard!

113
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,000
I know!

114
00:08:01,650 --> 00:08:03,710
I wished what I'm saying is nonsense.

115
00:08:05,740 --> 00:08:08,310
But you'll soon see
that I'm telling the truth.

116
00:08:08,310 --> 00:08:10,180
And when you do believe me,

117
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:13,870
please help me out.

118
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:17,200
Please help me.

119
00:08:21,590 --> 00:08:22,590
Taejun.

120
00:08:24,510 --> 00:08:25,880
I have to save Woojin.

121
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,320
You're insane.

122
00:09:17,710 --> 00:09:18,910
To-do list...

123
00:09:17,710 --> 00:09:21,870
[To-Do List]

124
00:09:19,510 --> 00:09:21,870
Make sure Lee Woojin
doesn't ride his bike.

125
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:31,800
[To-Do List]

126
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:25,180
Remind Lee Woojin to watch out for cars.

127
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:27,850
Never leave Lee Woojin alone.

128
00:09:31,060 --> 00:09:32,060
Make sure Lee Woojin

129
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,610
[To-Do List]

130
00:09:32,910 --> 00:09:34,710
doesn't go to my art cram school.

131
00:09:59,210 --> 00:10:00,210
Let's just

132
00:10:01,030 --> 00:10:02,690
get through this week safely.

133
00:10:10,180 --> 00:10:10,960
Huh?

134
00:10:11,170 --> 00:10:12,170
Why are you here?

135
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:14,510
To go to school with you.

136
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:17,250
Are you sure

137
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:18,550
nothing happened?

138
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:20,020
Of course.

139
00:10:20,330 --> 00:10:22,260
I just want to go to school with you.

140
00:10:22,980 --> 00:10:23,820
Yeah?

141
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:24,920
Let's go.

142
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:58,490
Hey,

143
00:10:58,610 --> 00:11:00,630
we're having class in the art room today.

144
00:11:00,630 --> 00:11:01,890
Let's get moving.

145
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:13,020
Art class, your favorite.

146
00:11:13,330 --> 00:11:13,900
Yeah.

147
00:11:16,410 --> 00:11:18,140
Guess the construction's done.

148
00:11:18,140 --> 00:11:19,750
Don't you want to go there?

149
00:11:20,230 --> 00:11:22,090
You said you left
something important there.

150
00:11:22,090 --> 00:11:23,090
Finally.

151
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:26,210
No, I don't need it anymore.

152
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:27,350
Hmm?

153
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:29,820
But we're screwed.

154
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:31,280
We didn't do the homework.

155
00:11:32,530 --> 00:11:33,610
I know.

156
00:11:34,270 --> 00:11:35,870
Because someone stood me up.

157
00:11:38,460 --> 00:11:39,060
Sorry.

158
00:11:40,090 --> 00:11:41,030
It's OK.

159
00:11:41,110 --> 00:11:43,710
We'll just apologize
to the teacher together.

160
00:11:44,170 --> 00:11:44,730
OK.

161
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:45,830
Let's go.

162
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:05,770
Aren't you leaving?

163
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:11,090
What are you doing?

164
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:14,810
I'm looking at you.

165
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:16,670
What?

166
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,060
You asked me to.

167
00:12:22,860 --> 00:12:23,860
[Won't you look at me?]

168
00:12:30,530 --> 00:12:31,610
Hey, that's...

169
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,270
Why'd you read it now?

170
00:12:33,290 --> 00:12:35,270
How can you take back what you gave?

171
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:36,890
Calm down. Give it to me.

172
00:12:36,890 --> 00:12:38,210
-No!
-Give it to me.

173
00:12:38,230 --> 00:12:38,430
No!

174
00:12:38,450 --> 00:12:39,540
Hey, give it to me!

175
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:42,840
Stop right there!

176
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:43,990
Bleh! I don't want to!

177
00:12:43,990 --> 00:12:45,430
I can catch you anyway.

178
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:49,380
Careful. You'll get hurt.

179
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:51,040
Here. Have it.

180
00:12:52,220 --> 00:12:54,880
You knew I'd wrestle it out of you
anyway, right?

181
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:56,340
It doesn't matter.

182
00:12:57,140 --> 00:12:58,240
Since I'm smart,

183
00:12:58,540 --> 00:13:00,040
everything's stored in my head.

184
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:00,570
Pfft.

185
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:04,100
This is so embarrassing.

186
00:13:06,230 --> 00:13:07,560
The bell's about to ring.

187
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,350
Let's go.

188
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,130
Alright, let me see what you've drawn.

189
00:13:22,530 --> 00:13:23,310
Wow.

190
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:24,450
This is interesting.

191
00:13:24,450 --> 00:13:24,930
Yeah?

192
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:26,630
Good job.

193
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:37,410
This is very original.

194
00:13:37,430 --> 00:13:37,860
Right?

195
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:39,480
Good brushwork too.

196
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:40,750
Good job.

197
00:13:54,690 --> 00:13:55,750
What about you two?

198
00:13:56,780 --> 00:13:58,640
Did you just draw in your minds?

199
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:01,190
-I'm sorry.
-I'm sorry.

200
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:03,760
Did I insist on a completed work?

201
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:06,160
You should've at least drawn something.

202
00:14:08,790 --> 00:14:10,120
-I'm sorry.
-I'm sorry.

203
00:14:10,590 --> 00:14:11,940
I'm sure you are. Tsk.

204
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:19,450
What are you trying to express?

205
00:14:29,370 --> 00:14:30,650
It's great now,

206
00:14:31,180 --> 00:14:32,560
but it'd be even better if

207
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:34,420
you could give it a bit more depth.

208
00:14:36,910 --> 00:14:38,310
OK, that's all for today.

209
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:41,300
Oh, right.

210
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:43,200
Before you leave,

211
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,930
I have an announcement to make.

212
00:14:45,170 --> 00:14:46,060
Anyone want to

213
00:14:46,070 --> 00:14:49,450
participate in an
environmental beautification art project?

214
00:14:49,450 --> 00:14:50,850
I need two volunteers.

215
00:14:55,910 --> 00:14:57,070
No one?

216
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:59,840
If you're into art,

217
00:15:00,070 --> 00:15:01,820
this is a great opportunity.

218
00:15:03,690 --> 00:15:04,560
Me!

219
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:07,240
Jang Hyeseong?

220
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,020
Yes.

221
00:15:08,330 --> 00:15:09,130
Right, you're

222
00:15:09,370 --> 00:15:11,360
planning to apply to art school, right?

223
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:11,770
Yes.

224
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:12,840
Great.

225
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,400
If you do a good job,

226
00:15:14,430 --> 00:15:16,080
I'll make a note of it
in your school report.

227
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:16,730
OK?

228
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:18,060
Thank you.

229
00:15:18,690 --> 00:15:19,920
Well, no one else?

230
00:15:20,270 --> 00:15:21,670
Sir, I'd like to do it with Woojin...

231
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:22,670
Sir!

232
00:15:22,940 --> 00:15:23,820
Me!

233
00:15:23,910 --> 00:15:24,640
Park Taejun?

234
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:25,430
Yes.

235
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:26,720
Hey.

236
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:28,810
This isn't your thing anyway.

237
00:15:28,810 --> 00:15:29,880
It is my thing.

238
00:15:30,970 --> 00:15:31,690
It is?

239
00:15:32,210 --> 00:15:32,970
Yeah.

240
00:15:33,610 --> 00:15:34,420
Then...

241
00:15:34,490 --> 00:15:35,730
will you do it with Taejun?

242
00:15:35,730 --> 00:15:38,110
But I want to do it with Woojin.

243
00:15:42,430 --> 00:15:44,430
Let's finish it together this time.

244
00:15:46,210 --> 00:15:46,910
Sure.

245
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:49,300
Let's finish it together this time.

246
00:15:49,660 --> 00:15:51,170
OK, I'll do it with him.

247
00:15:52,110 --> 00:15:53,710
Taejun, are you OK with that?

248
00:15:56,510 --> 00:15:57,510
Yes.

249
00:15:58,620 --> 00:16:00,300
If I keep at it,

250
00:16:00,870 --> 00:16:02,400
I'll get my chance someday.

251
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:03,540
It's settled then.

252
00:16:03,540 --> 00:16:05,740
Jang Hyeseong and Lee Woojin will do it.

253
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:07,330
-OK.
-OK.

254
00:16:07,410 --> 00:16:08,470
See you next class.

255
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,250
Thank you, sir.

256
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:13,150
You just decided for me?

257
00:16:13,710 --> 00:16:14,710
I'll help you.

258
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:16,140
It's a deal.

259
00:16:16,690 --> 00:16:17,690
Let's go. Come on.

260
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:26,120
Let's sit here.

261
00:16:32,730 --> 00:16:33,360
Ah.

262
00:16:33,640 --> 00:16:34,150
Here.

263
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:35,840
Thank you.

264
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:46,460
By the way,

265
00:16:47,780 --> 00:16:49,460
have you done a mural before?

266
00:16:50,390 --> 00:16:51,310
Yeah.

267
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:53,710
Oh, um...

268
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:55,280
Not for now.

269
00:16:56,170 --> 00:16:57,560
Not for now?

270
00:16:57,980 --> 00:16:58,980
What do you mean?

271
00:17:00,890 --> 00:17:01,890
Well, I mean,

272
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,360
we're going to do it soon.

273
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:05,359
Is there anything

274
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,359
you want to draw?

275
00:17:06,990 --> 00:17:07,859
Me?

276
00:17:09,390 --> 00:17:10,790
Of course, it has to be...

277
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:14,500
you.

278
00:17:35,460 --> 00:17:36,790
I want to draw you too.

279
00:17:47,770 --> 00:17:48,770
Then

280
00:17:48,850 --> 00:17:49,850
let's draw us.

281
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:52,250
Us?

282
00:17:52,330 --> 00:17:52,870
Yeah.

283
00:17:52,990 --> 00:17:53,990
Draw the two of us.

284
00:17:55,850 --> 00:17:56,670
OK.

285
00:17:59,930 --> 00:18:01,790
I think it'll take at least a week.

286
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:04,030
Hmm?

287
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,720
So for the next week,

288
00:18:09,380 --> 00:18:10,920
we have to stick together.

289
00:18:11,780 --> 00:18:12,780
Oh.

290
00:18:14,070 --> 00:18:14,870
OK.

291
00:18:15,330 --> 00:18:16,330
Got it.

292
00:18:48,050 --> 00:18:50,050
It'll take a long time to draw faces.

293
00:18:50,340 --> 00:18:52,200
How about drawing backs instead?

294
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:53,750
Backs?

295
00:18:53,940 --> 00:18:54,440
Yeah.

296
00:18:54,710 --> 00:18:55,710
Our backs.

297
00:18:57,580 --> 00:18:58,670
Don't you think

298
00:18:59,210 --> 00:19:00,530
that will look sad?

299
00:19:02,700 --> 00:19:03,960
Isn't it hopeful if you see it

300
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:05,160
as us moving forward?

301
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:08,460
Feels like a positive spin on it.

302
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:10,650
As they say,

303
00:19:11,070 --> 00:19:13,450
art is open to interpretation.

304
00:19:15,430 --> 00:19:16,430
OK then.

305
00:19:17,230 --> 00:19:18,230
Let's draw

306
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:20,220
our backs.

307
00:20:02,180 --> 00:20:03,180
Hey.

308
00:20:03,450 --> 00:20:04,450
Are you OK?

309
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:07,600
Yup!

310
00:20:07,990 --> 00:20:08,990
I'm OK.

311
00:20:11,580 --> 00:20:12,730
Pass me the yellow.

312
00:20:19,570 --> 00:20:20,440
Here.

313
00:20:24,460 --> 00:20:26,100
I asked for the yellow.

314
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:28,760
Oh, yellow...

315
00:20:37,180 --> 00:20:38,070
Hyeseong.

316
00:20:38,230 --> 00:20:40,160
When I draw the defense to the left,

317
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:41,610
make a pass to the right.

318
00:20:51,310 --> 00:20:52,230
Hey, Hyeseong!

319
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:54,130
Mine is the red ball, right?

320
00:20:54,350 --> 00:20:55,060
Yeah.

321
00:21:16,730 --> 00:21:17,600
Hyeseong.

322
00:21:20,470 --> 00:21:21,550
Are you

323
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:23,640
maybe

324
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:24,700
color-blind

325
00:21:24,730 --> 00:21:25,730
or color-weak?

326
00:21:28,460 --> 00:21:29,160
What?

327
00:21:39,540 --> 00:21:40,600
Let's take a break.

328
00:21:43,020 --> 00:21:43,690
OK.

329
00:21:49,230 --> 00:21:50,230
Lee Woojin!

330
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:51,720
Jang Hyeseong!

331
00:21:53,270 --> 00:21:53,980
Wow.

332
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,730
So you're doing the mural here.

333
00:21:56,310 --> 00:21:57,080
Yeah.

334
00:21:57,740 --> 00:21:58,660
Why?

335
00:21:59,050 --> 00:22:00,090
I'm joining you.

336
00:22:02,370 --> 00:22:04,370
But the art teacher asked us to do it.

337
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:07,320
I just asked the art teacher
for permission.

338
00:22:07,450 --> 00:22:09,050
He said we can do it together.

339
00:22:09,460 --> 00:22:10,140
What?

340
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:12,570
The three of us together?

341
00:22:13,090 --> 00:22:13,690
Yeah.

342
00:22:14,650 --> 00:22:15,560
Can't I join?

343
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:17,740
Why must you join?

344
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:21,470
Because I want to do it with you too.

345
00:22:22,070 --> 00:22:23,130
But I don't want to.

346
00:22:29,830 --> 00:22:31,290
Hyeseong, what about you?

347
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:34,570
Hey.

348
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:35,960
Come on.

349
00:22:35,990 --> 00:22:37,090
This is unlike you.

350
00:22:41,010 --> 00:22:41,860
What?

351
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:43,830
I've always been like this.

352
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:03,000
[Epilogue]

353
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:05,130
Where on earth did he go?

354
00:23:10,050 --> 00:23:12,580
The person you have reached
is not available.

355
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,930
Why do you even have a phone?

356
00:23:21,520 --> 00:23:22,380
Woojin.

357
00:23:23,580 --> 00:23:24,980
Where's my baby brother?

358
00:23:31,970 --> 00:23:32,970
Hey, Taejun.

359
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:33,890
Eunha.

360
00:23:34,520 --> 00:23:35,390
Have you

361
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:36,670
met Hyeseong?

362
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:38,010
Ah...

363
00:23:38,320 --> 00:23:38,990
Yeah.

364
00:23:39,250 --> 00:23:40,600
Why did he go there?

365
00:23:40,620 --> 00:23:42,220
He was at school a minute ago.

366
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:43,410
I know, right?

367
00:23:44,290 --> 00:23:44,970
But

368
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:46,700
Hyeseong

369
00:23:47,180 --> 00:23:48,530
suddenly disappeared.

370
00:23:49,020 --> 00:23:50,020
What?

371
00:23:51,300 --> 00:23:52,360
Where did he go now?

372
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:53,720
I don't know.

373
00:23:54,660 --> 00:23:56,780
He just suddenly disappeared.

374
00:23:57,420 --> 00:23:58,170
What?

375
00:23:59,290 --> 00:24:06,340
[The late Lee Woojin]

376
00:24:02,930 --> 00:24:03,980
Where

377
00:24:04,980 --> 00:24:06,130
did Hyeseong go?

378
00:24:09,660 --> 00:24:10,660
Sigh.

379
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:17,020
At the moment, my vision turned white,

380
00:24:18,140 --> 00:24:20,470
and then Hyeseong suddenly disappeared.

381
00:24:22,090 --> 00:24:23,090
Something's off.

382
00:24:25,990 --> 00:24:26,870
Woojin!

383
00:24:28,030 --> 00:24:29,030
Hey, Lee Woojin!

384
00:24:35,460 --> 00:24:36,460
Jang Hyeseong?

385
00:24:38,030 --> 00:24:39,030
This time,

386
00:24:41,700 --> 00:24:42,970
I won't lose you again.

387
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:26,320
[Always Meet Again]

